    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'm going to close this after all. After spending much more time with these tests, I don't see much benefit in running them on multiple platforms. Knowing that it works on all of them and that our binaries pass bytecode comparison tests between these platforms already gives us high confidence that we'll catch platform-specific bugs.\r\n\r\nAlso, being constrained to shell syntax that is portable to both Linux and macOS would make them much more painful to write and maintain. If we want portability, we should rewrite them in Python instead.",
